decision_details:
-  this action plan has been prepared in consultation with and the cooperation of the relevant stakeholders of the Government as well as the civil society. This document not only provides a detailed policy and a legislative programme to realize  the fundamental rights and freedoms provided in the Constitution, but also looks to expand these rights and freedoms. This action plan mainly focuses on the following: 

		*	Civil and Political Rights;
		*	Economic Social and Cultural Rights;
		*	Prevention of Torture;
		*	Rights of Women;
		*	Migrant Workers;   
		*	Children; and,
		*	Internally Displaced Persons.

	The above Action Plan presented by Hon. Mahinda Samarasinghe, Minister of Plantation Industries, was approved by the Cabinet.
